        {
          "id": "fecbb0a6-62d5-4cb8-b33e-ff1e93d67be6",
          "title": "App Upgrade",
          "content": "# Dashboard Fixes Round 2\n\n* Fix greeting banner (\"Good Morning\") styling\n* Fix Focus Task card — larger buttons matching the screenshot\n* Fix Productivity Pulse — use line/area chart instead of bar squares\n* Fix Completion Trend chart — broken display\n* Fix modal z-index — backup popup overlapped by sidebar\n* Add System Logs filter by event type",
          "createdAt": "2026-03-16T03:03:34.034Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-03-16T03:37:18.460Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "170c6d30-a3e2-4ef1-883f-d1f98042193b",
          "title": "App update",
          "content": "### 1. **UI/UX & Aesthetics**\n\n* **`ui-ux-pro-max`** (![]()c:\\\\Users\\\\moamm\\\\OneDrive\\\\Desktop\\\\Test.agents\\\\skills\\\\ui-ux-pro-max\\\\SKILL.md)\n    * **Why**: It provides 50+ design styles and 21 palettes. It is essential for achieving that \"polished, premium Figma-inspired\" look and handling the complex layout of a design tool.\n* **`frontend-ui-dark-ts`** (![]()c:\\\\Users\\\\moamm\\\\OneDrive\\\\Desktop\\\\Test.agents\\\\skills\\\\frontend-ui-dark-ts\\\\SKILL.md)\n    * **Why**: Specifically focused on building high-end dark-themed interfaces with glassmorphism and smooth animations, perfect for the requested UI style.\n* **`frontend-design`** (![]()c:\\\\Users\\\\moamm\\\\OneDrive\\\\Desktop\\\\Test.agents\\\\skills\\\\frontend-design\\\\SKILL.md)\n    * **Why**: Ensures the interface has \"intentional aesthetics\" and a non-generic visual identity, moving away from standard HTML/CSS defaults.\n\n### 2. **Core Component & Interaction Logic**\n\n* **`web-artifacts-builder`** (![]()c:\\\\Users\\\\moamm\\\\OneDrive\\\\Desktop\\\\Test.agents\\\\skills\\\\web-artifacts-builder\\\\SKILL.md)\n    * **Why**: Designed for creating elaborate, multi-component React/Tailwind/shadcn/ui artifacts. This is perfect for building a standalone, complex web tool like an ASCII editor.\n* **`modern-javascript-patterns`** (![]()c:\\\\Users\\\\moamm\\\\OneDrive\\\\Desktop\\\\Test.agents\\\\skills\\\\modern-javascript-patterns\\\\SKILL.md)\n    * **Why**: Crucial for implementing the complex JS event listeners (`mousedown`, `mousemove`, `e.preventDefault()`), undo/redo state management, and the exact character-width calculations required for the ASCII grid.\n* **`javascript-mastery`** (![]()c:\\\\Users\\\\moamm\\\\OneDrive\\\\Desktop\\\\Test.agents\\\\skills\\\\javascript-mastery\\\\SKILL.md)\n    * **Why**: Provides deep knowledge on closures and async patterns which are vital for a performant \"Freehand\" tool and smooth performance while dragging.\n\n### 3. **Canvas & Rendering Specialized**\n\n* **`canvas-design`** (![]()c:\\\\Users\\\\moamm\\\\OneDrive\\\\Desktop\\\\Test.agents\\\\skills\\\\canvas-design\\\\SKILL.md)\n    * **Why**: Although it focuses on static art, its underlying knowledge of canvas API interactions is highly relevant for the rendering engine you need.\n* **`react-flow-node-ts`** (![]()c:\\\\Users\\\\moamm\\\\OneDrive\\\\Desktop\\\\Test.agents\\\\skills\\\\react-flow-node-ts\\\\SKILL.md)\n    * **Why**: Useful if you decide to implement the editor using a node-based architecture for its state, particularly for the \"Select/Move\" and \"Select/Move\" logic.",
          "createdAt": "2026-03-20T22:41:46.684Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-03-20T22:41:46.684Z"
        },
